## JWT Authentication Flow

```
POST /api/auth/register  →  { email, password, role, name }
  → bcrypt hash password → insert into users → return JWT

POST /api/auth/login     →  { email, password }
  → verify bcrypt → return JWT { userId, role, exp: 24h }

Protected routes use auth.middleware.js:
  → Extract Bearer token from Authorization header
  → jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET)
  → Attach req.user = { id, role }
  → Role check: if route requires 'regulator' and user is 'factory' → 403
```

**Farmers via WhatsApp** don't use JWT — they're identified by phone number in the webhook.

