## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Supabase vs Local Postgres for development**: Do you want to develop against your Supabase cloud instance directly, or set up a local PostgreSQL for dev and only use Supabase for production? Local is faster for development, but adds a migration step.

> [!NOTE]
> **Conversation state storage for WhatsApp bot**: The bot needs to remember where each farmer is in the "new → herb → quantity → photo" flow. Two options:
> 1. **In-memory Map** — simpler, but resets on server restart
> 2. **Supabase `conversation_state` table** — persistent, survives restarts
> 
> Recommend option 2 for production-readiness, but option 1 is fine for portfolio.

> [!NOTE]
> **Firebase Auth vs custom JWT**: Your prototype used Firebase Auth. The new plan uses custom JWT (bcrypt + jsonwebtoken). This is intentional — custom JWT is more impressive on a CV and you can explain the full auth flow in interviews. Confirming you're okay with this change.
